main event: A witness observed an oval-shaped object with a bright, bluish glow in Willsboro, New York on September 8, 1966.
interesting points: The object was heard when it came in and departed, and appeared several minutes later.
The description provided is vague and insufficient for a positive identification.
The witness estimated the object's speed to be 4-5 miles per hour and the distance to be about 1 mile.
The witness observed the object for about 30 minutes, but the sighting was not continuous.
There were three other witnesses who also saw the object, but their names were not provided.
sighted object: an oval-shaped object with a bright, bluish glow
